<h4>Alerts</h4>
<section class="styleguide-section">
  <p class="small">
    Alerts draw the user's attention to a specific condition, either prior
    to or in response to a user action.
  </p>
  <p class="small">
    The type of alert embodies the sentiment of the condition; the content
    reinforces good/expected behaviors or provides actionable information
    for bad/unexpected behaviors.
  </p>
  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Default</h4>
  <div class="alert ">
    <b>Hi.</b> I'm a nice little message for you.
  </div>


  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Info</h4>
  <div class="alert info">
    <b>Info.</b> Here's some great info for you!
  </div>


  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Success</h4>
  <div class="alert success">
    <b>Yay!</b> Here's the great thing you just did!
  </div>


  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Warning</h4>
  <div class="alert warning">
    <b>Caution!</b> Watch yourself, amigo!
  </div>


  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Error</h4>

  <div class="alert error">
    <b>Oh no!</b> Here's some bad news for you!
  </div>


  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Full Width Top</h4>

  <div class="alert alert-full-width-top">
    <b>Hi!</b> I can fill up the top of my entire parent container without looking odd!
  </div>


  <h4 class="h6 styleguide-subheader">Full Width Bottom</h4>

  <div class="alert alert-full-width-bottom">
    <b>Hi!</b> I can fill up the bottom of my entire parent container without looking odd!
  </div>
</section>
